      <h2>India's Hague Convention Status</h2>
      <p>India acceded to the Hague Convention on July 14, 2005. Since then, all Indian documents going to Hague member countries use the apostille system instead of embassy attestation.</p>

      <p>The MEA (Ministry of External Affairs) in India issues the apostille. This single certificate replaces the old process of UAE Embassy attestation in India. The UAE recognizes MEA apostille because both countries are Hague members.</p>

      <div class="info-callout">
        <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
        <div>
          <strong>What This Means Practically</strong>
          <p>You no longer need to visit the UAE Embassy in India for degree attestation. After HRD attestation, you go directly to MEA for apostille. This saves 1-2 weeks compared to the pre-2005 process.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>However, the UAE is NOT a Hague member. This means when you arrive in UAE with your apostilled degree, you still need MOFA attestation for government submissions. Learn more about <a href="/services/attestation/">UAE attestation requirements</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container content-container">
      <h2>The Attestation Chain for Indian Degrees</h2>
      <p>Indian degree attestation follows a strict five-step sequence. Each step must be completed in order before the next will accept your document.</p>

      <div class="attestation-chain">
        <div class="chain-steps">
          <div class="chain-step">
            <span class="step-num">1</span>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>University Verification</strong>
              <p>Your university registrar verifies the degree certificate is genuine. Most universities require an appointment. Processing takes 3-7 business days. The registrar stamps and signs the back of your certificate.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="chain-arrow"><i class="fas fa-arrow-down"></i></div>
          <div class="chain-step">
            <span class="step-num">2</span>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>HRD Attestation (State-Level)</strong>
              <p>The state HRD office attests the university's verification. You must use the HRD in the state where your university is located. Maharashtra HRD for Mumbai University, Tamil Nadu HRD for Anna University, etc. Processing: 2-15 days depending on state.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="chain-arrow"><i class="fas fa-arrow-down"></i></div>
          <div class="chain-step">
            <span class="step-num">3</span>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>MEA Apostille (Federal)</strong>
              <p>The Ministry of External Affairs issues the apostille certificate. This can be done at MEA offices in Delhi, Mumbai, Chandigarh, Kolkata, or Hyderabad. Cost: approximately INR 50. Processing: 1-3 business days. Online application available.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="chain-arrow"><i class="fas fa-arrow-down"></i></div>
          <div class="chain-step">
            <span class="step-num">4</span>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>Arabic Translation in UAE</strong>
              <p>The fully-attested degree must be translated into Arabic by an MOJ-licensed translator in UAE. This is required for MOHRE, GDRFA, and MOHESR submissions. The translation includes all stamps and signatures from steps 1-3. See our <a href="/personal/academic/degree/">degree translation service</a>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="chain-arrow"><i class="fas fa-arrow-down"></i></div>
          <div class="chain-step">
            <span class="step-num">5</span>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>UAE MOFA Attestation (If Required)</strong>
              <p>Some entities require MOFA attestation of the original apostilled degree. This is common for Golden Visa and MOHESR equivalency. Not all MOHRE employers require this step. Confirm with your receiving entity. Learn about <a href="/services/attestation/mofa/">MOFA attestation</a>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="warning-note">
        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
        <div>
          <strong>Critical Order:</strong> You cannot skip steps or complete them out of order. MEA will reject documents without HRD attestation. UAE authorities will reject documents without MEA apostille. The chain is unbreakable.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

