      <h2>Common Rejection Reasons</h2>
      <p>MOHRE and MOHESR reject thousands of Indian degrees each year. Most rejections stem from attestation errors or translation issues. Here are the top causes.</p>

      <div class="rejection-list">
        <div class="rejection-card">
          <div class="rejection-header">
            <span class="rejection-icon"><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i></span>
            <h3>HRD Stamp Missing or Wrong State</h3>
          </div>
          <p><strong>The Problem:</strong> Applicant skipped HRD attestation or used the wrong state HRD office. MEA apostille is present but HRD is missing.</p>
          <div class="solution">
            <strong>Solution:</strong> You cannot add HRD attestation after MEA apostille. The document must be redone from step 1. Always complete HRD before MEA.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rejection-card">
          <div class="rejection-header">
            <span class="rejection-icon"><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i></span>
            <h3>University Not UGC-Recognized</h3>
          </div>
          <p><strong>The Problem:</strong> The degree is from a university not on the UGC (University Grants Commission) recognized list. MOHESR checks all Indian universities against the UGC database.</p>
          <div class="solution">
            <strong>Solution:</strong> Check the UGC website before starting attestation. Degrees from unrecognized universities will not pass MOHESR equivalency. Some may still be accepted for MOHRE work permits if HRD attested.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rejection-card">
          <div class="rejection-header">
            <span class="rejection-icon"><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i></span>
            <h3>MEA Apostille Doesn't Match Degree Name</h3>
          </div>
          <p><strong>The Problem:</strong> The degree certificate says "Suresh Kumar" but the MEA apostille document list says "Suresh K." MOHESR flags this as a mismatch.</p>
          <div class="solution">
            <strong>Solution:</strong> When applying for MEA apostille, ensure the document description exactly matches the degree certificate. Review the apostille certificate before leaving MEA office.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rejection-card">
          <div class="rejection-header">
            <span class="rejection-icon"><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i></span>
            <h3>Translation Name Doesn't Match Passport</h3>
          </div>
          <p><strong>The Problem:</strong> The Arabic translation uses a different name spelling than the passport. This is the most common rejection reason.</p>
          <div class="solution">
            <strong>Solution:</strong> Provide passport copy to translator. Insist on exact match. If your passport says "Suresh Kumar" with space, the translation should not combine as "SureshKumar" in English back-translation.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rejection-card">
          <div class="rejection-header">
            <span class="rejection-icon"><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i></span>
            <h3>Distance Learning Degree Without Proper Documentation</h3>
          </div>
          <p><strong>The Problem:</strong> The degree is from a recognized university's distance learning program, but MOHESR questions whether it meets in-person exam requirements.</p>
          <div class="solution">
            <strong>Solution:</strong> Submit additional documents showing the program was UGC-approved distance learning with supervised examinations. IGNOU, DDE degrees from major universities, and correspondence degrees from the 1990s face extra scrutiny. See our <a href="/resources/distance-education-uae/">distance education guide</a>.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rejection-card">
          <div class="rejection-header">
            <span class="rejection-icon"><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i></span>
            <h3>Provisional Certificate Submitted Instead of Final Degree</h3>
          </div>
          <p><strong>The Problem:</strong> Applicant submitted provisional certificate because final degree not issued yet. MOHESR does not accept provisional.</p>
          <div class="solution">
            <strong>Solution:</strong> Wait for final degree before starting attestation. MOHRE may accept provisional temporarily, but you must submit final degree within a specified period. MOHESR equivalency requires final degree only.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

